Maintainer: Naeem Khoshnevis <nkhoshnevis@g.harvard.edu>
Description: Provides a non-parametric Bayesian framework based on Gaussian process priors for estimating causal effects of a continuous exposure and detecting change points in the causal exposure response curves using observational data.
	Ren, B., Wu, X., Braun, D., Pillai, N., & Dominici, F., 2021. Bayesian modeling for exposure response curve via gaussian processes: Causal effects of exposure to air pollution on health outcomes. arXiv preprint <arXiv:2105.03454>.
